-- Rising Sun Seeks Bids for Construction of 2-Megawatt Hydroelectric Project
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2011-02-07T05:06:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-07/rising-sun-seeks-bids-for-construction-of-2-megawatt-hydroelectric-project.html
Rising Sun Power Pvt., an Indian
hydropower plant developer, is seeking bids for the construction
of a 2-megawatt project in southern Karnataka state.  Bids must be received by March 31 at 2 p.m. local time, the
Bangalore-based company said in an advertisement in the Business
Line newspaper.  Rising Sun is seeking vertical turbines for two plants of 1
megawatt each at Kanakapura Taluk on the Suvarnamukhi River in
Ramanagaram district, according to the advertisement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 